00:00:12.125 --> 00:00:16.020 align:middle line:90%


00:00:16.020 --> 00:00:18.180 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: This
conversation may be a bit

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:21.360 align:middle line:10%
in your face if you're a strict
adherent to biblical texts.

00:00:21.360 --> 00:00:24.780 align:middle line:84%
Paul Wallis, an Anglican
pastor and former archdeacon,

00:00:24.780 --> 00:00:26.580 align:middle line:84%
is a biblical scholar
and has helped

00:00:26.580 --> 00:00:30.990 align:middle line:84%
translate a story as to who
were the gods in the Bible.

00:00:30.990 --> 00:00:33.390 align:middle line:84%
They do not resemble what
I learned in Sunday school.

00:00:33.390 --> 00:00:34.600 align:middle line:90%
And why does this matter?

00:00:34.600 --> 00:00:36.870 align:middle line:84%
Because the same influences
are interfering with

00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:38.820 align:middle line:90%
humankind to this day.

00:00:38.820 --> 00:00:39.903 align:middle line:90%
Is that fair to say, Paul?

00:00:39.903 --> 00:00:41.903 align:middle line:84%
>> PAUL WALLIS: Yes,
that's fair to say, Regina.

00:00:41.903 --> 00:00:43.020 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: And welcome.

00:00:43.020 --> 00:00:44.520 align:middle line:90%
You've come from Australia.

00:00:44.520 --> 00:00:47.020 align:middle line:84%
I've interviewed you on
my side a couple of times.

00:00:47.020 --> 00:00:50.080 align:middle line:84%
But we haven't had a chance
to sit face to face before.

00:00:50.080 --> 00:00:51.570 align:middle line:90%
So this is fabulous.

00:00:51.570 --> 00:00:52.530 align:middle line:90%
It's a real treat.

00:00:52.530 --> 00:00:54.550 align:middle line:84%
>> WALLIS: It's great to be
in the same room with you.

00:00:54.550 --> 00:00:55.350 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:00:55.350 --> 00:00:58.590 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So here we are,
the word hermeneutics--

00:00:58.590 --> 00:00:59.610 align:middle line:90%
hermeneutics.

00:00:59.610 --> 00:01:03.270 align:middle line:84%
You're a religious educator that
specializes in hermeneutics.

00:01:03.270 --> 00:01:04.290 align:middle line:90%
What is hermeneutics?

00:01:04.290 --> 00:01:05.910 align:middle line:84%
Because I just
think of hermetics.

00:01:05.910 --> 00:01:07.320 align:middle line:90%
But that's not what it is.

00:01:07.320 --> 00:01:09.270 align:middle line:84%
>> WALLIS: Hermeneutics
is a great word.

00:01:09.270 --> 00:01:12.010 align:middle line:10%
It's the principles
of interpretation.

00:01:12.010 --> 00:01:16.390 align:middle line:10%
And so one of my roles in my 33
years in church-based ministry

00:01:16.390 --> 00:01:18.190 align:middle line:10%
was training pastors.

00:01:18.190 --> 00:01:20.710 align:middle line:84%
And I trained them in the
history of Christian thought

00:01:20.710 --> 00:01:21.880 align:middle line:90%
and hermeneutics.

00:01:21.880 --> 00:01:27.610 align:middle line:10%
So we would find the tools to
work out what's in the text.

00:01:27.610 --> 00:01:29.470 align:middle line:84%
How can we get out
of the text what

00:01:29.470 --> 00:01:33.050 align:middle line:84%
the writer intended instead
of us reading things in?

00:01:33.050 --> 00:01:35.350 align:middle line:84%
And so we would look
at source analysis.

00:01:35.350 --> 00:01:37.730 align:middle line:90%
Where does this text come from?

00:01:37.730 --> 00:01:40.000 align:middle line:90%
Is it the original form?

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:41.333 align:middle line:90%
If it isn't, how does it differ?

00:01:41.333 --> 00:01:42.133 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:01:42.133 --> 00:01:43.060 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:01:43.060 --> 00:01:45.610 align:middle line:84%
Form analysis, what kind
of literature is it?

00:01:45.610 --> 00:01:47.140 align:middle line:84%
And then the
linguistic question,

00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:48.650 align:middle line:90%
what do the words mean?

00:01:48.650 --> 00:01:51.430 align:middle line:84%
So these were the tools
that I explored with pastors

00:01:51.430 --> 00:01:53.320 align:middle line:90%
over 15-year period.

00:01:53.320 --> 00:01:55.810 align:middle line:84%
And it was those
skills that got me

00:01:55.810 --> 00:01:57.910 align:middle line:84%
into the whole world
of paleocontact,

00:01:57.910 --> 00:01:59.170 align:middle line:90%
which we're going to get into.

00:01:59.170 --> 00:02:00.550 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes, we are going to.

00:02:00.550 --> 00:02:02.900 align:middle line:90%
So first of all, let's begin--

00:02:02.900 --> 00:02:07.420 align:middle line:84%
we'll just start with all of
the names for God in the Bible.

00:02:07.420 --> 00:02:09.520 align:middle line:84%
Let's just start with
the names and how

00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:11.590 align:middle line:84%
they run parallel
to other texts,

00:02:11.590 --> 00:02:14.500 align:middle line:84%
such as Sumerian texts
and the Sky People,

00:02:14.500 --> 00:02:16.360 align:middle line:84%
because this
launches us right in.

00:02:16.360 --> 00:02:19.570 align:middle line:84%
>> WALLIS: Well, when we talk
about the Bible, people think,

00:02:19.570 --> 00:02:22.210 align:middle line:84%
oh, yes, that's
the book about God.

00:02:22.210 --> 00:02:25.390 align:middle line:84%
But if I were to
tell you that there

00:02:25.390 --> 00:02:31.120 align:middle line:84%
is no word in the Bible for a
transcendent creator spiritual

00:02:31.120 --> 00:02:33.520 align:middle line:90%
God, you might be surprised.

00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:36.550 align:middle line:84%
But there's no word
there that means that.

00:02:36.550 --> 00:02:39.640 align:middle line:84%
There are other words
that get translated as God

00:02:39.640 --> 00:02:41.830 align:middle line:90%
or the Lord or the Almighty.

00:02:41.830 --> 00:02:42.640 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Or gods.

00:02:42.640 --> 00:02:43.840 align:middle line:90%
>> WALLIS: Or gods.

00:02:43.840 --> 00:02:46.240 align:middle line:84%
But in my work, I've
gone to those words

00:02:46.240 --> 00:02:49.150 align:middle line:84%
and asked, what do
they mean at root?

00:02:49.150 --> 00:02:52.820 align:middle line:84%
Because if you start reading
lexicons, they'll tell you,

00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:55.600 align:middle line:84%
oh, this translation
is uncertain,

00:02:55.600 --> 00:02:59.540 align:middle line:84%
or this translation is
probably inaccurate.

00:02:59.540 --> 00:03:01.120 align:middle line:90%
So we go to the roots.

00:03:01.120 --> 00:03:05.530 align:middle line:84%
And the oldest word in the
Bible used for God is "Elohim."

00:03:05.530 --> 00:03:09.370 align:middle line:84%
And the roots mean
the powerful ones.

00:03:09.370 --> 00:03:11.110 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
you'll realize

00:03:11.110 --> 00:03:15.310 align:middle line:84%
that's why there are plural
behaviors, plural verb forms.

00:03:15.310 --> 00:03:18.700 align:middle line:90%
That's why God says let us make.

00:03:18.700 --> 00:03:21.700 align:middle line:84%
Let us make the humans
to look like one of us.

00:03:21.700 --> 00:03:22.660 align:middle line:90%
One of whom?

00:03:22.660 --> 00:03:24.650 align:middle line:90%
One of the powerful ones.

00:03:24.650 --> 00:03:26.110 align:middle line:90%
So that's Elohim.

00:03:26.110 --> 00:03:28.630 align:middle line:90%
Then there are the Bene Elohim.

00:03:28.630 --> 00:03:32.740 align:middle line:84%
Literally, that means the
sons of the powerful ones.

00:03:32.740 --> 00:03:35.170 align:middle line:84%
But the way it's
used suggests it's

00:03:35.170 --> 00:03:37.630 align:middle line:84%
like the sons and daughters
of the American Revolution.

00:03:37.630 --> 00:03:40.990 align:middle line:84%
It means the ones like,
having the characteristics of.

00:03:40.990 --> 00:03:42.970 align:middle line:84%
So we've got the ones
like the powerful ones.

00:03:42.970 --> 00:03:44.320 align:middle line:90%
That's the second wave.

00:03:44.320 --> 00:03:48.940 align:middle line:84%
Then you've got El
Elyon, the highest.

00:03:48.940 --> 00:03:51.640 align:middle line:84%
It means the powerful
one more senior

00:03:51.640 --> 00:03:53.140 align:middle line:90%
than the other powerful ones.

00:03:53.140 --> 00:03:54.850 align:middle line:90%
That's El Elyon.

00:03:54.850 --> 00:03:57.430 align:middle line:84%
You notice God hasn't
cropped up yet.

00:03:57.430 --> 00:04:00.970 align:middle line:84%
El Shaddai gets translated
as the Almighty,

00:04:00.970 --> 00:04:02.650 align:middle line:90%
doesn't mean that.

00:04:02.650 --> 00:04:05.380 align:middle line:84%
If you go to really
authoritative lexicons

00:04:05.380 --> 00:04:07.720 align:middle line:84%
like Brown-Driver-Briggs,
you will

00:04:07.720 --> 00:04:10.870 align:middle line:84%
find that it will
tell you that Almighty

00:04:10.870 --> 00:04:12.700 align:middle line:90%
is an invented translation.

00:04:12.700 --> 00:04:15.340 align:middle line:84%
It could mean the powerful
one of the mountains.

00:04:15.340 --> 00:04:17.589 align:middle line:84%
It could mean the powerful
one of the plains.

00:04:17.589 --> 00:04:20.140 align:middle line:84%
I argue in my book
"The Eden Conspiracy,"

00:04:20.140 --> 00:04:23.260 align:middle line:84%
it actually means the
powerful one, the destroyer.

00:04:23.260 --> 00:04:27.280 align:middle line:84%
So when he shows up,
introduces himself to Abraham,

00:04:27.280 --> 00:04:31.120 align:middle line:84%
his opening line is I'm the
powerful one, the destroyer.

00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:34.330 align:middle line:84%
Walk in front of me and
don't put a foot wrong.

00:04:34.330 --> 00:04:36.160 align:middle line:84%
And that's his
introduction to Abraham.

00:04:36.160 --> 00:04:38.540 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now, that's
where we still are today.

00:04:38.540 --> 00:04:38.830 align:middle line:90%
>> WALLIS: Yes.

00:04:38.830 --> 00:04:40.247 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Isn't
that interesting?

00:04:40.247 --> 00:04:41.590 align:middle line:90%
So when the destroyer comes--

00:04:41.590 --> 00:04:44.290 align:middle line:84%
and please share with us some
of the names of the one who

00:04:44.290 --> 00:04:46.450 align:middle line:90%
is known as the destroyer.

00:04:46.450 --> 00:04:49.660 align:middle line:84%
>> WALLIS: Well, El Shaddai,
the significance of that is,

00:04:49.660 --> 00:04:53.230 align:middle line:84%
I think, in that moment
where he meets Abraham,

00:04:53.230 --> 00:04:57.100 align:middle line:84%
it sets up this expectation
because we think that's God.

00:04:57.100 --> 00:04:59.140 align:middle line:84%
We now think we live
in a universe where

00:04:59.140 --> 00:05:02.620 align:middle line:84%
we have to tip toe
around for fear

00:05:02.620 --> 00:05:06.130 align:middle line:84%
of offending the Almighty,
the invented translation

00:05:06.130 --> 00:05:07.780 align:middle line:90%
because he's going to punish us.

00:05:07.780 --> 00:05:10.660 align:middle line:84%
He's going to throw us into
hell and torment us forever

00:05:10.660 --> 00:05:11.720 align:middle line:90%
if we get it wrong.

00:05:11.720 --> 00:05:15.220 align:middle line:84%
I think it goes back to that
moment where we read that

00:05:15.220 --> 00:05:17.150 align:middle line:90%
as a God text, and it isn't.

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:21.020 align:middle line:84%
And I think, as you're hinting,
the name of the destroyer

00:05:21.020 --> 00:05:23.420 align:middle line:90%
occurs all around the world.

00:05:23.420 --> 00:05:26.810 align:middle line:84%
You go to India,
talk about Shiva.

00:05:26.810 --> 00:05:29.790 align:middle line:84%
There are other names around the
world that mean the same thing.

00:05:29.790 --> 00:05:33.620 align:middle line:84%
And it's a recollection
of the same memory

00:05:33.620 --> 00:05:38.810 align:middle line:84%
in our cultural memory of times
when we were invaded, colonized

00:05:38.810 --> 00:05:41.810 align:middle line:84%
and overpowered by beings
that were not human.

00:05:41.810 --> 00:05:44.090 align:middle line:84%
And that didn't have
any empathy with us.

00:05:44.090 --> 00:05:48.110 align:middle line:84%
And that is a current through
the biblical narrative.

00:05:48.110 --> 00:05:50.450 align:middle line:84%
It's not the only kind
of contact we have,

00:05:50.450 --> 00:05:51.920 align:middle line:84%
because there are
other beings who

00:05:51.920 --> 00:05:55.610 align:middle line:90%
show up who are a lot nicer.

00:05:55.610 --> 00:05:58.340 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: We'll talk
about that as well.

00:05:58.340 --> 00:06:02.060 align:middle line:84%
The reason I love your work and
want to talk to you about this

00:06:02.060 --> 00:06:04.790 align:middle line:84%
is because, literally,
the world is still

00:06:04.790 --> 00:06:08.030 align:middle line:84%
divided into these
mindsets that we're

00:06:08.030 --> 00:06:11.570 align:middle line:84%
all given birth under
these same destroyer gods,

00:06:11.570 --> 00:06:13.250 align:middle line:84%
but pitting us
against each other

00:06:13.250 --> 00:06:16.080 align:middle line:84%
as though one person's
God is better than another

00:06:16.080 --> 00:06:19.650 align:middle line:84%
when we really all been raised
under the same influence

00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:23.620 align:middle line:84%
that we have to answer to that
is a master over our lives.

00:06:23.620 --> 00:06:25.800 align:middle line:84%
And I think most people
watching this by now

00:06:25.800 --> 00:06:28.050 align:middle line:90%
know that is not true.

00:06:28.050 --> 00:06:29.610 align:middle line:90%
>> WALLIS: No, that's not true.

00:06:29.610 --> 00:06:31.830 align:middle line:84%
And there's a very dramatic
moment in the Bible,

00:06:31.830 --> 00:06:35.550 align:middle line:84%
it comes in Deuteronomy
32 that tells you straight

00:06:35.550 --> 00:06:39.540 align:middle line:84%
away that the Elohim
have invaded our planet.

00:06:39.540 --> 00:06:41.820 align:middle line:84%
And they're now
carving up territory.

00:06:41.820 --> 00:06:45.570 align:middle line:84%
And El Elyon, the chief, is
giving this parcel of land

00:06:45.570 --> 00:06:47.370 align:middle line:84%
to this powerful one,
this parcel of land

00:06:47.370 --> 00:06:48.480 align:middle line:90%
to this powerful one.

00:06:48.480 --> 00:06:51.810 align:middle line:84%
And then the Yahweh
character gets a people group

00:06:51.810 --> 00:06:53.250 align:middle line:90%
with no land.

00:06:53.250 --> 00:06:55.740 align:middle line:84%
So he's in a foul
mood from that point

00:06:55.740 --> 00:06:58.470 align:middle line:84%
on because he's going to have
to wrestle some land off someone

00:06:58.470 --> 00:06:59.290 align:middle line:90%
else.

00:06:59.290 --> 00:07:01.470 align:middle line:84%
And so the human
beings get caught

00:07:01.470 --> 00:07:04.080 align:middle line:84%
in the conflicts
of these Elohim,

00:07:04.080 --> 00:07:06.330 align:middle line:84%
who are all jostling
up against each other

00:07:06.330 --> 00:07:08.100 align:middle line:84%
because they're
wanting resources.

00:07:08.100 --> 00:07:10.140 align:middle line:90%
They're wanting hegemony.

00:07:10.140 --> 00:07:12.960 align:middle line:90%
And we are their foot soldiers.

00:07:12.960 --> 00:07:15.570 align:middle line:84%
And so we've grown
up with this mindset

00:07:15.570 --> 00:07:19.170 align:middle line:84%
that we are here to serve
the higher ups and all

00:07:19.170 --> 00:07:21.360 align:middle line:84%
the arguments and
conflicts they have.

00:07:21.360 --> 00:07:23.970 align:middle line:84%
It gets even worse,
though, when we

00:07:23.970 --> 00:07:26.910 align:middle line:84%
translate that community
of warring individuals

00:07:26.910 --> 00:07:29.070 align:middle line:84%
and morph it into
a single entity.

00:07:29.070 --> 00:07:32.160 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yes, the only
God, the God Almighty.

00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:34.702 align:middle line:84%
>> WALLIS: Yeah, and so then
how do you explain the violence?

00:07:34.702 --> 00:07:36.535 align:middle line:84%
Then how do you explain
the lack of empathy?

00:07:36.535 --> 00:07:37.620 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: The brutality.

00:07:37.620 --> 00:07:39.330 align:middle line:90%
>> WALLIS: The brutality, yes.

00:07:39.330 --> 00:07:41.580 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: OK, so
this is something--

00:07:41.580 --> 00:07:44.290 align:middle line:84%
I'll just ask you at this
point before we go any further.

00:07:44.290 --> 00:07:49.590 align:middle line:84%
So as a person of substance in
the church, how in the world

00:07:49.590 --> 00:07:51.720 align:middle line:84%
did you ever explain
that to a congregation?

00:07:51.720 --> 00:07:56.020 align:middle line:84%
And I asked because by five,
I knew something was wrong.

00:07:56.020 --> 00:07:58.410 align:middle line:84%
I thought, no, if
there's a God, they

00:07:58.410 --> 00:08:01.470 align:middle line:84%
don't kill people, ask people
to give up their firstborn.

00:08:01.470 --> 00:08:03.450 align:middle line:90%
They would never be mean.

00:08:03.450 --> 00:08:04.410 align:middle line:90%
>> WALLIS: Exactly.

00:08:04.410 --> 00:08:06.390 align:middle line:90%
And children do pick that up.

00:08:06.390 --> 00:08:08.340 align:middle line:84%
Children will ask
these questions.

00:08:08.340 --> 00:08:12.210 align:middle line:84%
Why has God changed his mind
and decided to genocide everyone

00:08:12.210 --> 00:08:13.230 align:middle line:90%
with a flood?

00:08:13.230 --> 00:08:16.620 align:middle line:84%
Why is God punishing
70,000 innocent people?

00:08:16.620 --> 00:08:18.300 align:middle line:90%
That's not right, is it?

00:08:18.300 --> 00:08:19.860 align:middle line:90%
Children pick this up.

00:08:19.860 --> 00:08:21.480 align:middle line:90%
They know there's something off.

00:08:21.480 --> 00:08:24.390 align:middle line:90%
And, well, preachers do as well.

00:08:24.390 --> 00:08:25.320 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:08:25.320 --> 00:08:27.362 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: How do they
keep the story going then?

00:08:27.362 --> 00:08:30.768 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how did you feel
personally when you--

00:08:30.768 --> 00:08:32.700 align:middle line:84%
>> WALLIS: When I came
against these texts?

00:08:32.700 --> 00:08:33.659 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:08:33.659 --> 00:08:38.039 align:middle line:84%
I, like a child, instinctively
knew these could not

00:08:38.039 --> 00:08:40.710 align:middle line:90%
be accurate stories about God.

00:08:40.710 --> 00:08:42.960 align:middle line:84%
And there was a
church father way back

00:08:42.960 --> 00:08:44.460 align:middle line:84%
in the beginning
of Christianity who

00:08:44.460 --> 00:08:47.460 align:middle line:84%
was considered to be the
father of hermeneutics.

00:08:47.460 --> 00:08:49.590 align:middle line:84%
And he came up with
a little schematic

00:08:49.590 --> 00:08:52.320 align:middle line:84%
to help preachers
with this problem.

00:08:52.320 --> 00:08:56.010 align:middle line:84%
And he was saying, if you
take the Elohim and Yahweh

00:08:56.010 --> 00:08:58.830 align:middle line:84%
stories at face value
as God's stories,

00:08:58.830 --> 00:09:01.500 align:middle line:84%
you'll have to believe
of God such things

00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:05.440 align:middle line:84%
as we would not believe of the
most savage and unjust of men.

00:09:05.440 --> 00:09:06.760 align:middle line:90%
So what do you do with it?

00:09:06.760 --> 00:09:08.730 align:middle line:84%
You look for another
layer of meaning.

00:09:08.730 --> 00:09:11.530 align:middle line:84%
You go for the
moral of the story.

00:09:11.530 --> 00:09:13.492 align:middle line:84%
And if the moral of
the story is appalling,

00:09:13.492 --> 00:09:14.700 align:middle line:90%
you look for another meaning.

00:09:14.700 --> 00:09:16.350 align:middle line:90%
Is there a prophetic meaning?

00:09:16.350 --> 00:09:18.850 align:middle line:84%
Is it a metaphor
of something else?

00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:21.510 align:middle line:84%
So he's given this
helpful preacher's guide,

00:09:21.510 --> 00:09:24.750 align:middle line:84%
which is great if all you want
to do is produce a sermon.

00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:26.880 align:middle line:84%
And, therefore,
brothers and sisters

00:09:26.880 --> 00:09:29.890 align:middle line:84%
if that's what you're
looking for, fine.

00:09:29.890 --> 00:09:32.190 align:middle line:84%
But if you're wanting
to understand the text,

00:09:32.190 --> 00:09:33.810 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
to go back to it

00:09:33.810 --> 00:09:35.310 align:middle line:90%
and ask some deeper questions.

00:09:35.310 --> 00:09:38.850 align:middle line:84%
And the problem is that
most pastors are just as

00:09:38.850 --> 00:09:40.860 align:middle line:90%
overscheduled as everyone else.

00:09:40.860 --> 00:09:42.690 align:middle line:90%
They'll come across the text.

00:09:42.690 --> 00:09:44.928 align:middle line:84%
They'll find a way to
preach around it and think,

00:09:44.928 --> 00:09:46.470 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have
to get back to that

00:09:46.470 --> 00:09:48.400 align:middle line:84%
and work out what's
really going on there.

00:09:48.400 --> 00:09:50.430 align:middle line:84%
And then they never
do get back to it.

00:09:50.430 --> 00:09:53.310 align:middle line:84%
And it was really only
because I was invalided out

00:09:53.310 --> 00:09:55.530 align:middle line:84%
for a while with an
ultimate Frisbee injury

00:09:55.530 --> 00:09:59.160 align:middle line:84%
that I had the opportunity to
go back to some of these texts

00:09:59.160 --> 00:10:01.440 align:middle line:84%
and think, well, what
really is happening there?

00:10:01.440 --> 00:10:05.310 align:middle line:84%
If it's not a God story,
what is it a story about?

00:10:05.310 --> 00:10:09.230 align:middle line:84%
What was it our ancestors
wanted to know here?

00:10:09.230 --> 00:10:13.030 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And so by allowing
that story to stand--

00:10:13.030 --> 00:10:16.300 align:middle line:84%
others, not yourself-- by
allowing that story to stand,

00:10:16.300 --> 00:10:21.340 align:middle line:84%
it is essentially
justified colonization

00:10:21.340 --> 00:10:26.258 align:middle line:84%
of every kind from virtually
the beginning of modern history.

00:10:26.258 --> 00:10:27.550 align:middle line:90%
>> WALLIS: That is the problem.

00:10:27.550 --> 00:10:29.080 align:middle line:90%
That's exactly the problem.

00:10:29.080 --> 00:10:33.160 align:middle line:84%
If we read these stories of
colonization and violence--

00:10:33.160 --> 00:10:35.620 align:middle line:84%
and all colonization
is violent--

00:10:35.620 --> 00:10:40.060 align:middle line:84%
but interpret it as a God story,
it distorts our image of God.

00:10:40.060 --> 00:10:43.120 align:middle line:84%
So instead of God being a
beautiful idea, the source

00:10:43.120 --> 00:10:45.400 align:middle line:84%
of the cosmos and everything
in it, that in which

00:10:45.400 --> 00:10:48.350 align:middle line:84%
we all live and move and have
our being, all of a sudden,

00:10:48.350 --> 00:10:52.360 align:middle line:84%
we've got this violent
entity who can be brutal,

00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:55.300 align:middle line:84%
can't be reasoned with,
is actually unforgiving,

00:10:55.300 --> 00:10:57.370 align:middle line:84%
and does things
that really can't

00:10:57.370 --> 00:11:00.550 align:middle line:84%
be justified morally,
except if he's God,

00:11:00.550 --> 00:11:02.120 align:middle line:90%
you have to justify it.

00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:07.180 align:middle line:84%
So if God is xenophobic, you
have to justify xenophobia.

00:11:07.180 --> 00:11:11.240 align:middle line:84%
If God thinks in terms
of the human race divided

00:11:11.240 --> 00:11:13.820 align:middle line:84%
into my people
and not my people,

00:11:13.820 --> 00:11:16.340 align:middle line:84%
you have to start
thinking in the same way.

00:11:16.340 --> 00:11:18.090 align:middle line:84%
And, Regina, you're
absolutely right.

00:11:18.090 --> 00:11:20.450 align:middle line:84%
You can draw a
straight line from that

00:11:20.450 --> 00:11:22.940 align:middle line:84%
to all the conquests
we've made, invading

00:11:22.940 --> 00:11:25.550 align:middle line:84%
each other's countries,
enslaving other people groups,

00:11:25.550 --> 00:11:27.860 align:middle line:84%
all kinds of misogyny
and injustice

00:11:27.860 --> 00:11:32.510 align:middle line:84%
done in the name of God
because that's how God behaves,

00:11:32.510 --> 00:11:33.450 align:middle line:90%
isn't it?

00:11:33.450 --> 00:11:34.250 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:11:34.250 --> 00:11:38.000 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: What a perfect point
to bring up because most people

00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:40.430 align:middle line:84%
think, how could this be
done in the name of God?

00:11:40.430 --> 00:11:41.990 align:middle line:90%
But you just explained it.

00:11:41.990 --> 00:11:44.150 align:middle line:84%
If you're looking
at the God the way

00:11:44.150 --> 00:11:47.810 align:middle line:84%
I was taught about God in Sunday
school, I found it terrifying.

00:11:47.810 --> 00:11:51.470 align:middle line:84%
I hated those stories
and murder and blood

00:11:51.470 --> 00:11:53.870 align:middle line:84%
running down the
streets and locusts

00:11:53.870 --> 00:11:55.950 align:middle line:90%
and giving up your first born.

00:11:55.950 --> 00:11:56.750 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:11:56.750 --> 00:11:58.000 align:middle line:90%
>> WALLIS: Well, that's right.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:00.470 align:middle line:84%
And the moment
you allow yourself

00:12:00.470 --> 00:12:03.300 align:middle line:84%
to consider the possibility
it's not a God story,

00:12:03.300 --> 00:12:06.350 align:middle line:84%
the moral evaluations
are obvious.

00:12:06.350 --> 00:12:08.660 align:middle line:90%
A genocide is a genocide.

00:12:08.660 --> 00:12:10.887 align:middle line:84%
A brutalization is
a brutalization.

00:12:10.887 --> 00:12:12.470 align:middle line:84%
And I remember my
daughter coming home

00:12:12.470 --> 00:12:14.060 align:middle line:90%
from school one day.

00:12:14.060 --> 00:12:17.420 align:middle line:84%
And they were going to a
Christian school in Canberra,

00:12:17.420 --> 00:12:18.770 align:middle line:90%
Australia, at the time.

00:12:18.770 --> 00:12:21.530 align:middle line:84%
And they'd done a
Bible study in class.

00:12:21.530 --> 00:12:24.470 align:middle line:84%
Now, I think Evie was
10 when this happened.

00:12:24.470 --> 00:12:28.730 align:middle line:84%
And they'd studied a text
where God had just slaughtered

00:12:28.730 --> 00:12:30.170 align:middle line:90%
another bunch of people.

00:12:30.170 --> 00:12:34.260 align:middle line:84%
And the students were asking,
isn't a God a God of love?

00:12:34.260 --> 00:12:35.450 align:middle line:90%
Why would he do that?

00:12:35.450 --> 00:12:37.670 align:middle line:90%
And the teacher gave his answer.

00:12:37.670 --> 00:12:40.700 align:middle line:84%
And my daughter Evie
said, I wasn't really

00:12:40.700 --> 00:12:43.500 align:middle line:90%
convinced by what he said.

00:12:43.500 --> 00:12:45.830 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, did
you ask a question, Evie?

00:12:45.830 --> 00:12:49.040 align:middle line:84%
And she said, yes, I put
up my hand, and I said,

00:12:49.040 --> 00:12:50.870 align:middle line:90%
would God do that?

00:12:50.870 --> 00:12:54.200 align:middle line:84%
How could you justify
that in the name of love?

00:12:54.200 --> 00:12:56.640 align:middle line:84%
And I said, what
did the teacher say?

00:12:56.640 --> 00:12:58.260 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
he gave an answer.

00:12:58.260 --> 00:13:01.670 align:middle line:84%
But I'm not sure he really
believed what he was saying.

00:13:01.670 --> 00:13:04.400 align:middle line:90%
So we all have that instinct.

00:13:04.400 --> 00:13:05.630 align:middle line:90%
Children have it.

00:13:05.630 --> 00:13:09.290 align:middle line:84%
But the translations have
kind of bullied believers

00:13:09.290 --> 00:13:14.160 align:middle line:84%
into not asking the questions,
because you can't question God.

00:13:14.160 --> 00:13:17.040 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So we're
talking about, certainly,

00:13:17.040 --> 00:13:20.970 align:middle line:84%
most of the developed world for
sure in terms of the religions

00:13:20.970 --> 00:13:24.600 align:middle line:84%
and some of the other
cultures that have come up

00:13:24.600 --> 00:13:26.400 align:middle line:90%
socioeconomically behind.

00:13:26.400 --> 00:13:29.790 align:middle line:84%
Nonetheless, all the
Judeo-Christian religions,

00:13:29.790 --> 00:13:33.990 align:middle line:84%
the Muslim faith, all under
these brutal gods, although I

00:13:33.990 --> 00:13:38.940 align:middle line:84%
don't really know enough about
