of all of those cultures

00:13:48.750 --> 00:13:51.210 align:middle line:84%
an innate sense
of low self-esteem

00:13:51.210 --> 00:13:53.040 align:middle line:90%
just to be born human.

00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:56.680 align:middle line:84%
>> WALLIS: Yes, you are made
to feel guilty for having been

00:13:56.680 --> 00:13:57.480 align:middle line:90%
born.

00:13:57.480 --> 00:13:59.980 align:middle line:84%
So this whole doctrine
of original sin,

00:13:59.980 --> 00:14:03.120 align:middle line:84%
which is a total distortion
of what's in the Bible,

00:14:03.120 --> 00:14:07.050 align:middle line:84%
means that you don't have to do
anything wrong in order for you

00:14:07.050 --> 00:14:10.540 align:middle line:84%
to have to feel ashamed of
yourself, and not only that,

00:14:10.540 --> 00:14:14.290 align:middle line:84%
but to believe that your whole
purpose is to serve the higher

00:14:14.290 --> 00:14:17.330 align:middle line:90%
ups, serve God ultimately.

00:14:17.330 --> 00:14:20.320 align:middle line:84%
But it becomes something
that's very easy to manipulate.

00:14:20.320 --> 00:14:23.260 align:middle line:84%
So we have churches where
people can be manipulated.

00:14:23.260 --> 00:14:25.210 align:middle line:84%
And we have whole
societies where

00:14:25.210 --> 00:14:28.730 align:middle line:84%
we're wired to serve somebody
better than ourselves.

00:14:28.730 --> 00:14:33.910 align:middle line:84%
I mean, my gran, she grew up--
she was a Downton Abbey era

00:14:33.910 --> 00:14:34.750 align:middle line:90%
person.

00:14:34.750 --> 00:14:37.390 align:middle line:84%
And she began her life
in service working

00:14:37.390 --> 00:14:39.220 align:middle line:90%
in one of those great houses.

00:14:39.220 --> 00:14:43.120 align:middle line:84%
And I remember seeing a
documentary about that period.

00:14:43.120 --> 00:14:46.880 align:middle line:84%
They were interviewing
servants about the families

00:14:46.880 --> 00:14:47.680 align:middle line:90%
they had served.

00:14:47.680 --> 00:14:49.090 align:middle line:90%
And there was this big house.

00:14:49.090 --> 00:14:53.830 align:middle line:84%
Five people lived in the house,
and 50 servants served them.

00:14:53.830 --> 00:14:57.370 align:middle line:84%
And that was seen as
normal, acceptable.

00:14:57.370 --> 00:15:00.350 align:middle line:84%
They interviewed some of
these servants years later.

00:15:00.350 --> 00:15:02.110 align:middle line:90%
They were in their 70s and 80s.

00:15:02.110 --> 00:15:03.850 align:middle line:84%
And the interviewer
said, you talk

00:15:03.850 --> 00:15:07.780 align:middle line:84%
as if the five in the
family were better than you.

00:15:07.780 --> 00:15:10.690 align:middle line:90%
Oh, well, they were, they said.

00:15:10.690 --> 00:15:13.870 align:middle line:84%
I thought, better
in what respect?

00:15:13.870 --> 00:15:15.340 align:middle line:90%
Better morally.

00:15:15.340 --> 00:15:16.780 align:middle line:90%
Were they more intelligent?

00:15:16.780 --> 00:15:19.630 align:middle line:84%
It was just this wiring
that we are all here

00:15:19.630 --> 00:15:22.820 align:middle line:84%
to serve someone more
powerful, wealthier,

00:15:22.820 --> 00:15:24.370 align:middle line:90%
more important than ourselves.

00:15:24.370 --> 00:15:27.940 align:middle line:84%
And it goes back to
this worldview of a God

00:15:27.940 --> 00:15:30.280 align:middle line:84%
who demands obedience
and service and us

00:15:30.280 --> 00:15:31.420 align:middle line:90%
all tiptoeing around.

00:15:31.420 --> 00:15:33.010 align:middle line:90%
But it's a distortion.

00:15:33.010 --> 00:15:37.300 align:middle line:84%
And I love going to the root
meanings of the key words

00:15:37.300 --> 00:15:40.090 align:middle line:84%
and realizing that
the stories are really

00:15:40.090 --> 00:15:41.080 align:middle line:90%
about something else.

00:15:41.080 --> 00:15:43.450 align:middle line:84%
They're really about how
unacceptable that is.

00:15:43.450 --> 00:15:47.230 align:middle line:84%
They're really about finding
our power as individuals

00:15:47.230 --> 00:15:50.860 align:middle line:84%
and discovering each other and
discovering our people power.

00:15:50.860 --> 00:15:53.830 align:middle line:84%
And there are inspiring
moments of people power

00:15:53.830 --> 00:15:56.440 align:middle line:84%
in the Bible, all
of which disappear

00:15:56.440 --> 00:16:00.812 align:middle line:84%
the moment you start translating
Yahweh and El Shaddai as God.

00:16:00.812 --> 00:16:03.020 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Let's talk about
the people power that was

00:16:03.020 --> 00:16:06.060 align:middle line:84%
originally there that
has gone missing.

00:16:06.060 --> 00:16:09.590 align:middle line:84%
>> WALLIS: There's a powerful
moment in 1 Samuel 8.

00:16:09.590 --> 00:16:13.520 align:middle line:84%
And it's a moment in
which the tribes of Israel

00:16:13.520 --> 00:16:17.870 align:middle line:84%
have just got fed up of that
scenario I was just describing.

00:16:17.870 --> 00:16:20.900 align:middle line:84%
They don't want to
serve Yahweh anymore.

00:16:20.900 --> 00:16:26.780 align:middle line:84%
He's had enough, virgin girls,
gold, beef, and lamb off them.

00:16:26.780 --> 00:16:28.820 align:middle line:84%
And they don't
want to be governed

00:16:28.820 --> 00:16:31.460 align:middle line:84%
by someone who doesn't have
any fellow feeling with them

00:16:31.460 --> 00:16:32.880 align:middle line:90%
any longer.

00:16:32.880 --> 00:16:35.660 align:middle line:84%
And so the leaders of
the tribes come together,

00:16:35.660 --> 00:16:37.940 align:middle line:84%
and they confront
Yahweh's deputy.

00:16:37.940 --> 00:16:40.280 align:middle line:90%
And they say, it's enough.

00:16:40.280 --> 00:16:42.960 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to
serve Yahweh anymore.

00:16:42.960 --> 00:16:47.190 align:middle line:84%
We're going to have a human
leader for human society.

00:16:47.190 --> 00:16:52.610 align:middle line:84%
And in that moment, Yahweh
knows he's lost his power.

00:16:52.610 --> 00:16:55.400 align:middle line:84%
Up until that point, he's
governed through terror,

00:16:55.400 --> 00:16:56.810 align:middle line:90%
through violence.

00:16:56.810 --> 00:16:59.780 align:middle line:84%
And now he has a bunch of
people who have clearly

00:16:59.780 --> 00:17:05.550 align:middle line:84%
made a decision which amounted
to, what can he do, kill us?

00:17:05.550 --> 00:17:08.040 align:middle line:84%
And they've reached the
point where that attitude

00:17:08.040 --> 00:17:10.619 align:middle line:90%
has transmuted into courage.

00:17:10.619 --> 00:17:11.970 align:middle line:90%
They're acting together.

00:17:11.970 --> 00:17:13.619 align:middle line:90%
They're speaking with one voice.

00:17:13.619 --> 00:17:17.819 align:middle line:84%
And when Yahweh sees that,
he realizes he has to go.

00:17:17.819 --> 00:17:19.020 align:middle line:90%
And so he goes.

00:17:19.020 --> 00:17:21.750 align:middle line:84%
He's replaced with
human kings and queens,

00:17:21.750 --> 00:17:23.579 align:middle line:90%
but the story goes on.

00:17:23.579 --> 00:17:28.590 align:middle line:84%
And the lesson in the story is
the persistence of old powers

00:17:28.590 --> 00:17:31.720 align:middle line:84%
because Yahweh might not
be their king anymore.

00:17:31.720 --> 00:17:35.230 align:middle line:84%
But he's still defining
their foreign policy.

00:17:35.230 --> 00:17:37.020 align:middle line:84%
He's still telling
the kings and queens

00:17:37.020 --> 00:17:38.550 align:middle line:90%
what they can and can't do.

00:17:38.550 --> 00:17:41.490 align:middle line:84%
If public policy departs
too far from what he wants,

00:17:41.490 --> 00:17:44.220 align:middle line:84%
he hoicks it back
to what he wants.

00:17:44.220 --> 00:17:47.040 align:middle line:84%
And this resonates with me
having grown up in Britain,

00:17:47.040 --> 00:17:50.160 align:middle line:84%
because in Britain,
for 800 years,

00:17:50.160 --> 00:17:52.980 align:middle line:84%
we've been trying to
get rid of crown power.

00:17:52.980 --> 00:17:55.530 align:middle line:84%
We've been trying to
become a democracy.

00:17:55.530 --> 00:17:58.800 align:middle line:84%
And after 800 years
of major changes,

00:17:58.800 --> 00:18:03.030 align:middle line:84%
revolutions, Magna Carta,
getting rid of the monarchy,

00:18:03.030 --> 00:18:06.850 align:middle line:84%
redefining the monarchy, we've
had all the social movements,

00:18:06.850 --> 00:18:10.390 align:middle line:84%
the labor movements, two
world wars, a Reformation,

00:18:10.390 --> 00:18:14.320 align:middle line:84%
even now, our democratically
elected prime minister

00:18:14.320 --> 00:18:16.900 align:middle line:84%
can't go more than
a week before having

00:18:16.900 --> 00:18:20.290 align:middle line:84%
to report to the crown what
he or she has been up to.

00:18:20.290 --> 00:18:23.350 align:middle line:84%
Nothing can become law
unless the senior member

00:18:23.350 --> 00:18:25.570 align:middle line:90%
of the Windsor family says, OK.

00:18:25.570 --> 00:18:29.320 align:middle line:84%
We now know that her late
Majesty Queen Elizabeth

00:18:29.320 --> 00:18:33.190 align:middle line:84%
II blocked about 160
pieces of legislation

00:18:33.190 --> 00:18:35.350 align:middle line:84%
until she'd got
exemptions from them.

00:18:35.350 --> 00:18:38.890 align:middle line:84%
And they were laws to do
with workers' rights, animal

00:18:38.890 --> 00:18:39.880 align:middle line:90%
welfare.

00:18:39.880 --> 00:18:42.340 align:middle line:84%
There was a law introduced
in the '60s saying

00:18:42.340 --> 00:18:44.620 align:middle line:84%
it's illegal to
discriminate against people

00:18:44.620 --> 00:18:47.440 align:middle line:84%
in the workplace on the
basis of their ethnicity.

00:18:47.440 --> 00:18:49.420 align:middle line:84%
Or the queen wouldn't
have any of that,

00:18:49.420 --> 00:18:52.100 align:middle line:84%
had to get an exemption
before that could become law.

00:18:52.100 --> 00:18:54.640 align:middle line:84%
So don't tell me that's
ceremonial power.

00:18:54.640 --> 00:18:56.992 align:middle line:84%
That's crown power
that is persisting.

